inn1.comm: good length around off stump, a tidy start, the batsman moves forward to defend on the off side
good length a little further outside off, Watson lets it go
short of a length outside off, the ball climbs through to the keeper as Watson shoulders arms again
short and wide outside off, Watson is away with a cut off the back foot towards third man
fuller length but the line is too wide outside off for Haddin to play a shot at it
short and wide once again, Haddin uses the width to cut towards third man
full ball on off stump, driven off the front foot towards mid-off
a full ball angling into the right-hander, nearly in the blockhole, Haddin digs it out to Otieno
pushed off the front foot towards wide mid-on for a single
short ball and Watson stays firm in his crease, swivels and plays a muscular pull to the midwicket boundary
beautiful drive, gets on to the front foot to a full ball with a hint of outswing, the ball disappeared wide of the man at mid-off off the middle of the bat
the carnage begins, Watson sits back in his crease, waits for the short one, and pulls in flat over the midwicket boundary
defended towards mid-off but they take a quick single
good length on off stump, defended on the front foot towards the off
Odoyo is keeping Watson quiet with his line and length on off, Watson stays in his crease and defends
pushed off the front foot towards cover
Watson adjusts to the line of the ball close to off stump, and uses the shorter length to cut the ball late and fine of the fielder at third man

dropped in theory. Watson absolutely smashed the ball back at Odoyo who got his left hand to the ball. It was hit so hard that the ball carried in the air for a while after the deflection off the hand and went on the first bounce to the fielder at mid off
Haddin cuts loose, carving the ball off the front foot over point, that nearly carried all the way
short and wide, Haddin moves forward and slashes, he misses this time
good length and straight, Haddin moves back and defends with a straight bat
Haddin charges, two steps down, and thumps the ball through the line past the fielder at mid-on
dabbed from the crease with an open face behind point
played off the back foot towards the bowler
tight line and length around off stump, pushed off the front foot towards cover
fuller ball on off stump, driven to mid off on the front foot
played towards point off the back foot
tight over so far, Odoyo keeping wicket to wicket, Haddin defends from the crease
short of a length on off stump, Haddin stays on the back foot, gets behind the line and defends with a straight bat
sublime drive off the front foot, Haddin makes a bit of room to drive a length ball wide of the fielder at mid-off
in the blockhole, Watson digs it out towards midwicket and sets off
fired down leg side this time, the keeper dives to his right and pulls off a superb save with one hand
short of a length and straight, defended on the back foot
good length ball on off and middle, defended on the front foot towards mid-off
have Australia gone into a shell of sorts? Defended on the back foot towards the off again

dropped in theory again. Haddin played a firm straight drive low towards the bowler's right, Odhiambo got one hand to it on his follow through, which is more than most fast bowlers on display last night would have got on it
played off the pads towards midwicket
Watson moves forward and glides the ball towards third man
tight line and length on off and middle, defended on the front foot
blocked off the front foot back to the bowler
Haddin looks to drive on the off and ends up punching towards mid off
Haddin takes two steps forward, making room to hit through the off. He's a bit early and ends up pushing towards cover
played off the back foot on the leg side
a short of a length ball steered off the back foot behind point

caught! And such a late celebratory reaction from the keeper! That was short and wide from Odhiambo, but he got the ball to bounce a touch more. Watson went for the cut and got a thick edge through to the keeper, who had to take it over his head

loud appeal for lbw as Ponting misses the leg glance. The umpire says not out and Kenya ask for a review. Replays show that the ball is comfortably missing leg stump. It nearly missed the pad all together
a full ball outside off stump, Ponting lunges forward and plays the ball towards the bowler
Ponting moves forward and across and nudges a length ball towards midwicket
good length and straight at a brisk pace, Ponting defends on the back foot
defended on the front foot towards the off side
Haddin pushes the ball off the front foot towards mid-on and sets off
Ponting dabs the ball behind point and sets off, Collins Obuya makes a sharp save from a wide slip, forcing Haddin to send Ponting back. A direct hit and it would have been close
defended on the back foot on the off side
short ball and a bit too straight, Ponting swivels on the front foot and paddles the ball behind square for his first boundary
Ponting strides forward to a good length ball and punches towards cover
Haddin moves forward, as he's always looking to do, and drives to the fielder at mid off
excellent line and length, angling into off and middle from Odhiambo, Haddin moves back and defends

drama! Haddin pushes the ball on the off side, Ponting was backing up a bit too far so the fielder threw at the bowler's end and conceded an overthrow. as the Australians ran it, the throw came in from long on and hit direct at the bowler's end. Haddin is safe though
defended on the front foot towards mid-on
Ponting strides forward and plays a loose drive at a wide ball, not full enough to drive either. He gets beaten. Odhiambo's bowling at good pace
played back to the bowler off the front foot
Haddin charges and flays his bat at a good length ball, trying to hit over the off side. He was beaten and lucky that the ball didn't bowl him
full ball on off stump, driven wide of the fielder at mid-off, who is rather deep as well
a short and wide ball but the bounce is lower than usual and Ponting gets beaten as he tries to cut, the ball passed under his bat
defended on the front foot towards cover
Ponting strides forward to a good length ball and opens the face to steer the ball towards point
shot! Ponting strides forward, using the width of the length ball outside off to free his arms and lash it through point with a fierce square drive
played off the front foot towards the off side
the slower ball on off stump, Haddin defends watchfully towards the bowler
Odhiambo angles a good length ball into Haddin, not giving him the room he craves, and makes him defend on the leg side
excellent! Haddin backs away towards leg to make room, Odhiambo follows him with a full ball and Haddin gets a thick inside edge towards square leg
Haddin backs away again and steers a length ball towards third man by opening the face of his bat
Ponting strides forward and punches a length ball powerfully towards point where the fielder tumbles to his right to make the save
Haddin steps down and makes room to hit through the off, he ends up swishing lamely and gets beaten. He's moving a bit too much is Haddin
good length ball angling into the right-hander, Haddin defends on the leg side

edged and safe! Haddin comes down again, makes room, and slashes at a short of a length delivery outside off. The edge flies between the keeper and a wide first slip. Collins Obuya dives to his left at the wide first slip but can't reach it
steered towards third man for a single
Ponting strides forward a long way and defends towards point
Ponting slashes hard this time and hits the ball with the toe end of his bat into the ground towards first slip

a full ball and Haddin digs it out towards the off side and wants a risky single. Haddin would have been gone had there been a direct hit at the bowler's end, he stumbles and falls as he makes his ground
defended on the front foot towards the off
strays down leg this time and Ponting glances the ball off his pads to the fine leg-boundary
Ponting strides forward and pushes a good length ball from outside off towards point
Ponting moves forward again to a ball that is a touch shorter than the previous one and plays towards point

that's a rare slog from Ponting, drags a length ball from outside off high in the air over midwicket. He hasn't timed it well so the ball falls well inside the boundary and eventually reaches it after a mix-up in the field
There's that trigger movement from Haddin again, forward and towards leg to drive on the off. He hits it to mid-off where a fumble allows the single
Ponting moves across his stumps to work the ball off his pads on the leg side but can't make contact
Ponting drives off the front foot towards wide mid-off where there's a fumble once again from Odoyo. Looks a bit heavy, does Odoyo

that is a wonderful shot, he moves a long way outside leg and this time he uses the room to steer the ball behind point and wide of the fielder at third man. The keeper was standing deep and Haddin was standing out of his crease
this time Haddin walks forward and towards the off to swing a length ball powerfully through midwicket for four. The keeper needs to come back up, Haddin is moving freely out of his crease here
short of a length and slower, Haddin comes forward and mis-times the cut towards point
Ponting moves back and nudges the ball off his pads behind square
a quicker one on middle stump, Haddin gets an inside edge behind square as he tries to defend
Ponting strides forward to a slower ball and defends on the off side
a flighted delivery on off, drawing Ponting forward as he plays towards midwicket
Haddin moves forward and nudges the ball behind square for a single
Ponting goes back and defends the ball towards the bowler
worked off the pads behind square, Haddin wants one but short fine leg is too quick
driven off the front foot into a gap at cover
Ponting lunges forward and defends towards the bowler
Ponting moves across and nudges off the pads through the leg side
nudged off the front foot towards midwicket
played off the front foot towards midwicket
a touch too short and Ponting has time to move back and drive the ball in front of point, the fielder gives chase but in vain
Ponting lunges forward and across and nudges the ball on the leg side
Haddin stays in his crease and works the ball towards midwicket
Haddin stays back again and flicks the ball in front of square
that's fired down leg side, Ponting tried to paddle it but didn't get a touch on it
quite a bit of turn into the right-hander, Ponting defends on the front foot
played off the pads through midwicket
Ponting moves forward and defends towards midwicket
played off the front foot towards midwicket
Ponting comes forward and works the ball through square

loud appeal for lbw as Haddin moves across his stumps and tries to hoick the ball off the front foot over the leg side. Will Kenya review the not out decision? No they won't. Or have they? They've taken too long to decide ...
driven back firmly off the front foot towards the bowler
Haddin comes forward and swings the ball off his pads towards deep square
Ponting strides forward and blocks towards the bowler
Ponting gets on to the front foot and turns the ball off his pads behind square
Haddin defends on the front foot towards the off side
Haddin plants his foot forward, gets to the pitch of the ball, and swings it high over wide long-on. Sweetly timed and the ball clears the boundary. One-bounce four actually ...
played off the pads behind square for a single. Slight misunderstanding between the batsmen
swept behind square for a single
played off the back foot behind square for a single
Haddin gets to his half-century by dabbing the ball fine towards third man. Not the most fluent, but it's doing the job
defended back towards the bowler
defended on the front foot towards midwicket
the ball spins into Haddin and hits him on the pad as he tries to play on the leg side
short outside off stump and Haddin plays another deft dab to the third-man boundary
Ponting moves forward and pushes the ball from middle towards midwicket
Ponting misses the powerful sweep and gets hit on the pad
lots of turn into Ponting, sharp turn, and he nudges the ball off the back foot towards short third man
Haddin steps out and pushes the ball towards the bowler
superb timing! Haddin steps out and lofts the ball cleanly over the long-on boundary. There was a fielder there but cleared him comfortably
played towards point for a single
Haddin stays in his crease and defends on the leg side
Haddin drives on the front foot towards long off
nudged off the front foot towards midwicket
Ponting moves across and defends on the front foot
Ponting moves back, waits for the ball to turn and cuts towards short third man
pushed down to long on for a single
tossed up outside of, driven off the front foot towards cover
driven fluently off the front foot towards wide long-off
driven to long off this time for a single
driven off the front foot through point for a single
looped up on off stump, Ponting drives towards mid-off
that's a nice and lovely full toss on the pads, Ponting pushes it gently down the ground to long on. Friendly cricket all around.
defended from the crease on the leg side
played back to the bowler
Haddin moves forward and defends on the leg side
caught at deep midwicket! Haddin moves forward, picks up the ball from outside off and swings it high and straight to the man on the deep midwicket boundary
Clarke stays back and plays the ball off his pads towards short fine leg
almost, the fielder at midwicket dived but couldn't cut off Clarke's nudge off the pads
Clarke steps out and flicks the ball off his pads through square
played towards point from the crease
full toss, Clarke comes forward and mis-times the swat through the leg side

loud appeal for lbw as Ponting attempts to work the ball on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pad. The umpire says not out and Kenya want a review. That one didn't turn, was going straight through. A terrific review it is for that was hitting middle and leg.
White goes back and defends on the leg side
Obuya tosses one up so wide outside off, pitched beyond the wide lines
another high friendly full toss at chest height, White swats it tamely towards deep square leg. Friendly cricket all around.
forced off the back foot toward long off
driven off the front foot towards long off for a single
White gets on to the front foot and defends on the leg side
wide outside off stump and White cuts off the back foot through point
pushed off the front foot towards long on
he's strayed down leg side, Clarke misses the glance and the keeper misses the take
Clarke gets down the pitch and drives towards long on

oh wow! Did Kamande become Murali? White is shocked and with good reason. That ball pitched a long way outside off and spun viciously into the right-hander. White pushed forward in defence and the ball spun past his bat and hit off and middle. More middle than off. Was there an inside edge on to the stumps? I'm not yet sure ... There was no inside edge, simply spun massively between bat and pad.
played off the back foot to point
cut off the back foot through point for a single
a nice and high full toss and Hussey accepts the offering by driving through cover to get off the mark. Obuya's bowled a lot of these full tosses
short and wide outside off, Hussey waits on the back foot and cuts through cover
a massive long hop and Clarke simply waits and cuts through point
another full toss, Obuya suffering from the yips, Hussey plays towards cover where the fielder fumbles
driven towards mid on off the front foot
played off the pads through square leg
played off the pads towards short fine leg
bowled wide outside off stump, Clarke covers for the turn and lets it go. The ball does not turn
played off the pads past the fielder at short fine leg
played off the front foot towards point
driven off the front foot towards mid-off for a single
short ball on off, Clarke moves back and cuts towards point where the fielder mis-fields
too short and Hussey pulls powerfully off the back foot, the fielder at deep square slides to make the save
played off the pads behind square
excellent placement and timing. Clarke comes forward, takes the ball on the full, and drives past the fielder at mid-on
full toss and Clarke steps out and works it through midwicket
short ball this time on of, Clarke goes back and cuts through cover point
White steps out again and plays towards the bowler
driven off the front foot towards mid off
flat and a touch short, Hussey moves back and punches towards cover
driven off the front foot through cover for a single
defended on the back foot towards the bowler
Kamande stops before releasing that, cut off the back foot towards short third man
played off the pads behind square for a single
pitches outside leg and turns into the pads, Hussey stays back and plays the ball behind square
Clarke moves forward and then defends after failing to reach the pitch of the ball
played off the back foot through cover
Hussey plays back and works the ball off his pads through midwicket
Clarke works the ball off his pads through square and Hussey has to hurry and dive to complete the second
short ball and Hussey moves back and taps the ball towards long-off
Clarke moves forward and drives towards long off
Hussey moves back to work on the leg side and gets a leading edge towards the bowler
driven off the front foot through cover
driven off the front foot towards long on
played towards mid-off
played towards mid on this time
shorter and quicker, played off the back foot on the off side
worked off the pads through square leg for a single
Hussey moves back and works the ball off his pads through square
Clarke moves across his stumps to flick through square but misses and gets hit on the pad. The bowler appeals but that was missing leg
driven to long on for a single
short of a length outside off with the keeper standing up, Clarke cuts off the back foot and the fielder on the deep point boundary does splendidly to dive and save the four
Hussey ticks along with a cut off the back foot towards third man
terrific timing from Clarke who beats the man at extra cover with a drive from the crease
played back to the bowler
pushed off the back foot towards cover
Clarke drives fluently off the front foot for another single
Clarke moves forward and clips towards midwicket where the fielder dives and fumbles
played off the pads through square leg
flat and short, Clarke moves back and works the ball towards midwicket
flicked off the pads through square leg
Clarke moves back and nudges the ball through square leg
played off the back foot down the ground for a single
pitched far outside leg, Hussey goes back to pull down to fine leg but mis-times the shot
Clarke moves forward and drives towards long off for a single
fired down leg side and Hussey glances it fine to the boundary, easy as you please
Hussey moves back and pushes down the ground towards long off
played down the ground again for one more
left alone outside off stump
strays down leg side and this time Clarke gets a bit of bat on it to glance it fine past the keeper
Clarke moves forward and plays the ball off his toes through midwicket
Hussey tries to work the ball on the leg side off the back foot and misses, he gets hit on the pad and Kenya appeal. Will they review the umpire's not out decision? No they won't
down leg side again and Hussey works the ball fine past the keeper for four more
Hussey stays in his crease and plays the ball through point
fired in fast on middle and leg, defended on the front foot towards the bowler
driven off the front foot through cover
Odoyo beats Clarke's drive off the front foot and the ball beats the keeper as well, deflecting off his glove towards third man
worked off the back foot towards backward square
very wide down leg side ...
shorter length and Hussey plays a short arm jab towards midwicket
Hussey stays in his crease and dabs behind point
good length and straight, Clarke moves forward and drives past the bowler
full ball on the pads, Clarke misses out on the flick, that was there for the taking
wide down leg side, too far for Clarke to get bat on the ball
terrific cover drive, has the Hussey trademark all over it. Moves forward and makes crisp contact, forcing the fielders in the deep to dive to save the four
Clarke moves forward and taps the ball towards midwicket
short of a length, angling into the body. Clarke turns it off his hips to reach a half-century, off 52 balls. A fluent innings
pitches outside leg and angles into the pads. Hussey plays it towards square leg
Hussey tries to run a good length ball that angles across him towards third man, but gets beaten
full ball on off and middle, Clarke drives off the front foot towards mid-off
a touch short and Hussey plays the short arm pull towards deep midwicket
a full toss but Hussey's drive can't beat the fielder at cover
pushed past the bowler from the crease for a single
played off the back foot towards cover point for one
played off the back foot towards the bowler
a full toss and Hussey smashes the ball through square leg with a perfectly-placed pull shot
nudged off the pads towards fine leg for a single
terrific shot, Clarke moves forward and towards the off, the ball was on his pads and he flicks it over the fielder at short fine leg for four, the 100 partnership comes up
Clarke moves forward and drives towards long on
Hussey turns a full ball off his pads behind square for a single
a useful yorker, Clarke can't do much with that but dig it out
well played Huss! Gets to his fifty by forcing the ball off the back foot through cover. He's been a dynamo in Australia's middle order and they love it that he's back
played past the bowler for a single, that was in the air towards Odoyo but a touch high, it went off the leading edge
Hussey pulls off the back foot and the fielder in the deep spots the ball racing across the turf rather late
full ball angling into middle stump, flicked off the front foot towards deep midwicket
Clarke backs away to make room and hit a length ball through the off side, he misses and the keeper also fails to collect it
Hussey strides forward and drives through cover

caught at long-on! The length was a touch full, the line was outside off and the pace might have been a touch slower. Hussey drags the ball from outside off towards David Obuya who ran in a bit and took the catch. Hussey was aiming to hit it straighter ...
a high full toss and Clarke moves across and whips it off his hips towards the fine leg boundary
Clarke moves forward and nudges the ball towards midwicket
pushed off the front foot towards point for a quick single. A direct hit at the bowler's end would have dismissed him
shot, Clarke makes room by moving towards leg and cuts a length ball from the stumps behind point
a full toss and Clarke clips it off his pads toward deep midwicket
worked off the pad behind square for a single
Smith barely moves his feet as he prods this one back to the bowler
full ball on middle, driven towards long-on for a single
played off the back foot towards long on for one
strays down leg side, Smith tries to nudge it but gets hit on the pad
worked off the pads through midwicket
short ball outside off, Clarke gets into position early and pulls it cleanly into the gap between deep midwicket and long on
a high full toss and Clarke mis-times his pull off the front foot, it goes towards long-on and falls short of the fielder
another full toss, and this time Clarke does it, pulling the ball and timing it well enough to cause a flutter in the people beyond the midwicket boundary
Clarke steers the ball towards third man where the fielder has a bit of work to do
Clarke moves forward and flicks the ball through square for a single
Smith flicks the ball off his pads but doesn't make contact actually, leg byes. Now why is a team rewarded when the batsmen doesn't hit the ball?
short of a length and Smith lines up the pull but fails to connect
full toss and Smith makes room and smashes it to the man on the cover boundary
the bowler strays on to the pads, Clarke moves across and attempts to glance but misses it
Clarke moves outside leg to make room and lofts a ball that follows him towards long-on
Clarke moves towards leg and drives a length ball with lots of power, the fielder at cover, Kamande, dives to his right and makes an outstanding save
a slower ball and Clarke had finished the pull by the time the ball arrived. Odhiambo beams in delight
smashed with power to the man on the long-on boundary
a slower ball from round the wicket, worked off the body behind square
Smith clears his front foot out of the way and aims to hit the ball over the midwicket boundary. Instead, he gets an inside edge past the keeper to bring up the 300
Smith gets cramped for room with this line from round the wicket and mis-times the pull behind square
Clarke moves across and works the ball off his pads behind square
Smith makes room by moving towards leg and drives straight to long-on, where a fumble allows the second

whoops, he's holed out to long-on. Clarke tried to launch a full ball over the man on the long-on boundary. He didn't get enough elevation or distance and Patel took a fine catch at shin height. That was travelling to him quickly and Clarke's World Cup average comes down a notch or two ...
pushed off the front foot through point for a single
full ball outside off stump, Smith mis-times the drive towards cover
Johnson launches a length ball over cover, high over cover, and the ball beats Patel on the wide long-on boundary. That bounced and spun away and over him
fuller and slower, pushed towards the off for a single

that's gone miles in the air! Smith plays some curious shots. He cleared his front foot out of the way and attempted an almighty slog. He was aiming over midwicket but the ball went in the direction of square leg
short ball and Johnson pulls towards deep midwicket
that was a very slow ball and it kept very low and hit Smith on the pad, it would have missed off stump
The ball angled into the left-hander and Johnson's attempt at smashing it towards midwicket missed. The ball hit his pad and went towards short third man
punched toward long on for a single
full ball and on the pads, Johnson glances it fine past the fielder at short fine leg
short ball outside off stump, Johnson swats it towards deep midwicket

inn2.comm: outswing at brisk pace, Ouma fishes and misses, that angled in towards the stumps before curving away past the bat
Kenya are away, Lee gets a bit too straight but this time the ball doesn't swing as much, played off the pads through square leg
banged in short outside off stump, Ouma begins to play it and then lets the ball pass
another fast outswinger at 146kph, the line was outside off and it veered away sharply, Haddin has to move quickly to collect
full and straight from Lee on off stump, pushed towards cover point from the crease
Ouma pushes forward and gets a thick outside edge towards third man
short of a length, pushing the batsman on the back foot, played towards cover
Clarke missed at the non-striker's end or else the batsman was a goner, he pushed towards point and set off for a risky single
Tait's pace is not giving the batsman any time to do anything but stay in the crease and block. That was 144 kph
played off the back foot towards mid-off, the length was full but the batsman stayed in his crease, 147 kph ...
a forceful shot off the back foot but it is to the fielder at cover
the short ball banged down leg side
Tait pitches short of a length but strays down leg side once again
short and wide outside off stump, Obanda flashes and flashes hard, slashing the ball hard and flat over the third-man boundary.
Lee bowls the yorker at 145 kph, it's on target but Ouma digs it out
full and straight again from Lee at searing pace, played towards square leg
good length just outside off, defended from the crease on the leg side
Lee sends down a bouncer at 138 kph, forcing the batsman to duck

edged ... and taken! Lee follows the bouncer with a full ball that begins to swing away from the batsman from around off stump. Ouma chases after it with the drive and edges to Haddin who takes a simple catch. Excellent ball after that bouncer. Full and swinging at pace.
defends a good length delivery towards the bowler
a full and fast ball down leg side again. Tait's radar is wonky today.
a short of a length ball angles into the batsman and hits him high on the pad and thigh at 148 kph
that pull is pre-meditated but he's made good contact with the length ball and placed it through midwicket

that is a monstrous hit! Obanda take a bow, you've hit it on the roof! Well not really but it went miles. Tait bowled a length ball and Obanda launched it off the front foot several rows back over the long-on boundary. That was a slower ball.
short ball outside off, looks to cut but gets beaten
Tait responds with the bouncer and Obanda avoids it
bowled him! Tait bowls a fast full toss. That was there to be hit and Obanda wanted to send it over the leg-side boundary. He missed it though and the ball crashed into middle stump
Lee hits the pad with a good length ball but that was missing leg
flicked through square leg for a single
he moves forward to drive a full ball towards point where the fielder dives to take the pace off the ball
short of a length from Lee and quite straight, Collins Obuya gets behind the line and defends
Lee hits the pad with a full and fast delivery but that was sliding down leg as well
Lee swings a full ball into the right-hander, on middle stump, line, the batsman defends with a straight bat
the bouncer and David Obuya ducks under it
that was full and fast outside off at 146 kph, the ball hit bat rather than the other way around as  David Obuya swatted outside off stump
Tait fires another full ball but it's on the pads and hits them before going towards fine leg
short of a length but wide outside off stump, left alone by the batsman
Tait angles a full ball into the right hander, Collins Obuya barely moves before bringing his bat down in time to squirt the ball through square
good length but outside off, Collins Obuya lets it go through to Haddin
full ball outside off and Collins Obuya pushes it in front of point
Lee fires in another yorker, which Obuya - David - manages to keep out
full and straight, the batsman plays it back towards the bowler, Lee fields on his follow through
another yorker from Lee and once again it's kept out, played to midwicket
short of a length and just outside off, David Obuya fishes and misses
short of a length on the hips, fended on the leg side
fuller length and it's driven off the front foot to the fielder at point
ah now that's the widest wide of the World Cup. Haddin has to dive a long way to his right to collect it
now this one is down leg side, Johnson's radar is wonky too.
much better, good length around off stump, played off the back foot on the off side
Collins Obuya drives loosely at one that angles across him without moving his feet. It was a full ball and it beat him
once again Collins Obuya pushes forward at a full ball that slants across him and gets beaten
this is fuller and much wider outside off, Collins Obuya lets it go
short of a length and straight, he gets behind the line and defends with a straight bat
full ball outside off stump, Collins Obuya drives it behind point and even Lee's graceful, athletic slide on the boundary can't stop the four. Over to brother David now.
a sharp and well directed bouncer, forcing David to duck for cover
Lee pitches on a good length and is very straight, defended on the leg side from the crease
length ball outside off, mis-timed towards cover off the front foot
good length on a tight line outside off stump, the batsman has to play it and he pokes tentatively off the back foot, the outside edge goes towards third man
David Obuya moves forward and swats a length delivery through cover for four, nicely timed and placed well
defended from the crease towards cover and that is an extremely well-run single
full ball just outside off, played off the front foot towards mid-off
a well-directed bouncer, over the stumps, the batsman ducks under it
nice shot! David Obuya moves a touch across and flicks the ball off his pads through square leg, good use of the wrists

there's a mix-up between the brothers and David Obuya is run out. David pushed the ball off his hips towards midwicket and sprinted for the run. Collins, perhaps seeing that Hussey was sprinting towards the ball from square leg with no signs of hamstring trouble, did not want the run. David kept coming and by the time he stopped and turned, Hussey had reached the ball. his throw to Haddin was good and David had to go.

tragic way to go, Mishra is run out. It was perhaps the only way Australia were going to strike. Obuya dabbed the ball towards backward point and the batsmen decided to take on Clarke. Bad move. He swooped on the ball and hit the stumps direct at the striker's end. Well played Mishra, an innings ended by a bad decision to run. He's made his highest ODI score today.

Lbw! surely? No there's an inside edge. It was full and straight and Odoyo moved right across his stumps and got hit on the boot, after an inside edge
